HEADWORD: musth
<hw>musth</hw></mhw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧st)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Hind. <ets>mast</ets> intoxicated, ruttish, fr. Skr.
<ets>matta</ets>, p.p. of <ets>mad</ets> to rejoice, intoxicate.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Being in a condition of dangerous frenzy,
usually connected with sexual excitement; -- said of adult male
elephants which become so at irregular intervals, typicaly due to
increased testosterone levels.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The condition of frenzy.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An elephant in
must.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mustac</ent>⟦br⟧
